      • nextNamingFunction

        public static Label nextNamingFunction(Label label,
                                       int prefixLength,
                                       int treeLength)
        Γ(μ) is the set of possible prefixes of μ Γ(μ, D) set of possibile prefixes with maximum length D Notation: μ = label, x = prefix Locates the first bit in the suffix of μ (with respect to x) that differs from x’s ending bit; the value nextNamingFunction(μ, x) is then the prefix of μ, which ends up with this located bit. fnn(x, μ) = p00∗1 ∈ Γ(μ) if x = p0, p11∗0 ∈ Γ(μ) if x = p1. Intuitively, fnn locates the first bit in the suffix of μ (with respect to x) that differs from x’s ending bit; the value nextNamingFunction(μ, x) is then the prefix of μ, which ends up with this located bit.
        Parameters:
        label -
        prefixLength -
        treeLength -
        Returns:
